Discoveries
Sigma.js + Graphology Integration
- Sigma v3.0.2 uses imperative API (new Sigma(graph, container, settings)) — no React bindings in sigma itself
- @react-sigma/core@5.0.6 exists as separate package but was NOT used — imperative API chosen for more control over re-layout on filter changes
- graphology-layout-forceatlas2 API is forceAtlas2.assign(graph, opts) NOT forceAtlas2.run() — the .run() method does not exist
- graphology-layout circular layout: circular.assign(graph, { scale: 300 })
- Sigma requires SSR disabled — WebGL2RenderingContext is not defined on server. Must use next/dynamic with ssr: false
- No "sigma/styles" CSS import exists in sigma v3 — only @react-sigma/core/lib/style.css exists (for React wrapper). We don't import any sigma CSS.
- Build with sigma works: /graph renders as ○ (static) with client-side WebGL hydration
Markdown Content Rendering
- react-markdown@10.1.0 + remark-gfm@4.0.1 + rehype-highlight@7.0.2 installed
- API route at /api/document-content/[id] reads actual file from disk using fs.readFile
- REPO_ROOT env var (defaults to S:/self-organizing-library) + entry.path resolves to actual file
- Only renders files with extensions in: .md, .mdx, .txt, .json, .yaml, .yml, .js, .ts, .tsx, .jsx, .css, .sh
- Files over 500KB return truncated message instead of content
- Non-markdown files render as <pre><code> blocks; markdown files render with ReactMarkdown
